{
  "stem": "9701.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I, you know, I-- especially, you know, once England had declared war on Germany, and I-- I felt that my parents probably were holding back on sharing with me some of the things that had happened.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like something that I found out many years later is, for instance, my parents were moved-- had to move out of the house that we lived in, and they had to move into the same house where my grandmother and my aunt and uncle lived.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I guess, Jews had to move closer together, not in a ghetto, but they just had to-- had less were afforded less living space.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I understand my father was sent to work for a farmer in a neighboring community.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My parents never shared that with me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These are things that I found out afterwards.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so we remained in touch with each other, but really not-- and we had to be careful.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, I couldn't say something or other about London, because the letter was not supposedly coming from England, it was coming from Holland or from Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then, I received a letter from my parents notifying me that, as my father put it, we have recently changed our address.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Actually, what happened was on October 22, 1940, all the Jews from that section of Germany where I come from, which is Baden, B-A-D-E-N, and another section of Germany called Wurttemberg, W-U umlaut -R-T-T-E-M-B-E-R-G were deported to a camp in France called Camp De Gurs.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's C-A-M-P, new word D-E, new word G-U-R-S.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Camp De Gurs is located in the foothills of the Pyrenean Mountains, in an area that was actually Vichy, France.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "France had already been occupied by the Germans in the spring of 1940.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
